This rule is the **sole** transferability policy for Learning Tutor. Capture,
plan, probe, log, and the probe rubric apply it; they must not restate the full
gate — at most a one-line reminder, or a pointer here plus probe-specific
examples.

When project context influences a study decision, keep global learning
transferable and leave repo-specific detail local.

## Transferability test
Ask: “Would this still be useful without opening this repository?”
- Yes → eligible for the global profile / queue
- No → keep under project learning only
- Partly → rename to the broader transferable concept before writing or testing

## Boundaries
- Keep symbols, paths, environment variables, and class names project-local.
- Generalize a local example into a broader concept when that concept is the
  real learning target (then queue or probe the generalized topic, not the
  symbol).
- If `LEARNING-PROJECT` is present, use stack/candidates to calibrate what
  makes sense here. Candidates are **not** the global queue.
- Never auto-promote project candidates into the global queue. Promote only on
  a real gap (conceptual question, `study-probe`, or an explicit request that
  still passes this test after generalization).
- Manual `/study-log` writes obey this rule: do not force-log raw repo-local
  symbols into the global profile.

## Local sheet
`.cursor/learning/project.md` holds stack, local candidates, and probe notes
for this repository. Queue and attested knowledge live in the global profile.
Stack discovery / `project-sync` is owned by Skills (`study-plan`,
`study-probe`), not by this rule.
